# Technical Report

## 1. Model Selection

For object detection, YOLOv8s was used due to its balance between speed and accuracy. It provides reliable detection of players in dynamic sports scenes.

## 2. Tracking Algorithm

DeepSORT was used for multi-object tracking. It combines motion prediction using Kalman filtering and appearance-based re-identification to assign persistent IDs.

## 3. Why YOLO + DeepSORT

This combination is widely used in real-world applications because YOLO provides fast and accurate detections, while DeepSORT ensures ID consistency across frames.

## 4. ID Consistency

ID consistency is maintained using:

* max_age parameter to retain tracks during occlusion
* n_init to avoid false positives
* appearance feature matching

## 5. Challenges Faced

* Occlusion caused ID switching
* Motion blur reduced detection confidence
* Similar-looking players confused tracker

## 6. Failure Cases

* Players overlapping for long duration
* Sudden camera movement
* Low-resolution frames

## 7. Improvements Implemented

* Confidence filtering (score > 0.5)
* Frame skipping for stability
* Trajectory visualization
* FPS and object count display

## 8. Future Work

* ByteTrack integration
* Heatmap generation
* Speed estimation
* Multi-class tracking
